This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.00100. This field is required when getNsxTier0Gateway() or any of getIngressCidrs(), getEgressCidrs() are specified.       • getEgressCidrs

        public java.util.List<InstancesTypes.Ipv4Cidr> getEgressCidrs()
        CIDR blocks from which NSX assigns IP addresses used for performing SNAT from container IPs to external IPs. These ranges should not overlap with those in getNamespaceNetworkCidrs(), getIngressCidrs(), or other services running in the datacenter. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.00100. This field is required when getRoutedMode() is set to False and getNsxTier0Gateway() or any of getNamespaceNetworkCidrs(), getIngressCidrs() is specified. When getRoutedMode() is set to True, this field is not allowed. An update operation only allows for addition of new CIDR blocks to the existing list.

        The current value of the property.
